data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** The test confirms both work without needing `unsafe` — you can write:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signed   = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[4];
```

The only caveat is that `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context (since the size varies by platform), but `stackalloc` itself works fine in safe code. On this 64-bit system, each `nint`/`nuint` is 8 bytes.
